==Savlaow politek ha brysyow pennskrifek==
Nyns yw ''The Guardian'' omgelmys gans parti politek, mes yw livrel yn tradicyon.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2008/nov/17/political-affiliation-guardian-observer Political affiliation], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 17 mis Du 2008, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref> Yn 2005, 48% a'n redyoryon a'n paper o votoryon [[Parti Lavur|Lavur]] ha 34% o votoryon [[Parti Livrel Werinel|Gweriniethoryon Livrel]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090523104959/http://www.ipsos-mori.com/content/polls-05/voting-intention-by-newspaper-readership-quarter-1.ashx Voting Intention by Newspaper Readership Quarter 1 2005], ''Ipsos MORI'' (yn Sowsnek), 21 April 2005, kovskrifys a[http://www.ipsos-mori.com/content/polls-05/voting-intention-by-newspaper-readership-quarter-1.ashx 'n derowel] war 23 mis Me 2009, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref>

An paper a skoodhyas yn krev [[Tony Blair]] y'n 1994 etholans ledyorieth Parti Lavur,<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/1994/jul/02/labour.uk Labour: The choice for the future], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 2 mis Gortheren 1994, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref> hag y'n 1997 etholans ollgemmyn.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/1997/may/02/electionspast.comment A political earthquake], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 2 mis Me 1997, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref> Y'n [[Dewisyans ollgemmyn Ruwvaneth Unys, 2010|2010 etholans ollgemmyn]], ''The Guardian'' a skoodhyas [[Nick Clegg]] h'an [[Parti Livrel Werinel]].<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2010/apr/30/the-liberal-moment-has-come General election 2010: The liberal moment has come], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 30 mis Ebrel 2010, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref> Ev a skoodhyas [[Ed Miliband]] ha'n [[Parti Lavur]] y'n 2015 etholans ollgemmyn,<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/may/01/guardian-view-britain-needs-new-direction-needs-labour The Guardian view: Britain needs a new direction, Britain needs Labour], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 1 mis Me 2015, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref> hag a'y wosa [[Yvette Cooper]] y'n 2015 etholans ledyorieth Lavur.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/aug/13/guardian-view-labour-leadership-choice-yvette-cooper-jeremy-corbyn The Guardian view on Labour’s choice: Corbyn has shaped the campaign, but Cooper can shape the future], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 13 mis Est 2015, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref> ''The Guardian'' a skoodhyas [[Brexit|an kaskyrgh remaynya]] y'n [[Unyans Europek]].<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/may/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-eu-debate-david-cameron-makes-a-serious-case The Guardian view on the EU debate: David Cameron makes a serious case], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 9 mis Me 2016, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref> An paper a skoodhyas [[Jeremy Corbyn]] ha'n Parti Lavur y'n [[Dewisyans ollgemmyn Ruwvaneth Unys, 2017|etholansow ollgemmyn 2017]] ha [[Dewisyans ollgemmyn Ruwvaneth Unys, 2019|2019]], mes ev a skoodhyas ynwedh votys rag an [[Parti Kenedhlek Alban]], [[Plaid Cymru]], an Parti Livrel Werinel po an [[Parti Gwer]] yn ranndiryow heb chons krev a drygh Lavur.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/ng-interactive/2017/jun/02/the-guardian-view-on-our-vote-its-labour The Guardian view on the election: it’s Labour], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 2 mis Metheven 2017, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/ng-interactive/2019/dec/10/the-guardian-view-on-general-election-2019-a-fleeting-chance-to-stop-boris-johnson-in-his-tracks The Guardian view on general election 2019 A fleeting chance to stop Boris Johnson in his tracks], ''The Guardian'' (yn Sowsnek), 10 mis Kevardhu 2019, kyrghys 27 mis Genver 2022</ref>

